A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Reverend Dr. Homer Lee Mitchell Sr.; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
4 with the passing of Reverend Dr. Homer Lee Mitchell Sr. on January 25, 2025; and
5 WHEREAS, Reverend Dr. Homer Lee Mitchell Sr. was born on December 19, 1934, in
6 Pittsview, Alabama, a beloved son of Jessie and Bertha Mitchell; and
7 WHEREAS, he began his professional career as a civil service employee at Fort Moore,
8 Georgia, before answering his divine calling to ministry in 1972 and delivering his trial
9 sermon at Antioch Baptist Church in Pittsview; and
10 WHEREAS, his pastoral journey began in 1973 when he was called to lead three
11 churches—Liberty Hill Baptist Church in Phenix City, Alabama; Antioch Baptist Church in
12 Columbus, Georgia; and Rising Star Baptist Church in Marvyn, Alabama—faithfully
13 managing their alternating service schedules before becoming the full-time pastor of Antioch
14 Baptist Church in 1983; and
